--- !u!114 &1676711835
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 88901f3538a5bce48819d3f8fc1e9bfb, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::AnswerOptionsSO
  Answer1Text: A little kid bounced way too high and was flying over the safety wall.
    I dove to catch him, caught him perfectly, but cracked my head right on a concrete
    garden gnome
  Answer2Text: Busy, kind of exhausting, but nice. I spent most of my time trying
    to make children smile and helping my aunt with her rent
  Answer3Text: I dressed up as a bootleg spider-hero for low-budget children's parties.
    The fabric was incredibly itchy
  Answer4Text: I didn't even have time to change out of my work outfit. It's wrinkled
    and smells faintly of juice boxes and sweat
  Answer5Text: It's a plastic kid's colored hat from the party! I was holding it
    for the birthday boy. Can you make sure he gets it back?
